  - m_Id: 4605696233472
    m_Localized: Fps_counter
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 4662000570368
    m_Localized: Language
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 4842825404416
    m_Localized: Russian
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 4923620282368
    m_Localized: Graphics
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5038644875264
    m_Localized: Audio
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5071930871808
    m_Localized: Music
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5104378007552
    m_Localized: Concierge
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5174473216000
    m_Localized: Anna
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5208799399936
    m_Localized: Artem
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5236414697472
    m_Localized: Erich
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5270308868096
    m_Localized: Good morning. Sorry for the unexpected visit.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5386574974976
    m_Localized: Everything's fine. Did something happen?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5393181003776
    m_Localized: The local police officer came to see you early this morning. He
      said he had important information for you. He tried to contact you, but couldn't
      get through. Then he was called away somewhere.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5506565623808
    m_Localized: He asked me to give you this flash code. It will give you access
      to the data they left specifically for you.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5490253975552
    m_Localized: The local police officer? Ah... I didn't receive any notifications.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5522499784704
    m_Localized: Did he say something about Artyom?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5537968377856
    m_Localized: Unfortunately, no, I just emphasized that it is necessary to hand
      it over to you personally.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5551692140544
    m_Localized: What if I have questions for him personally?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5567131373568
    m_Localized: He said he'd be in the office after two o'clock. You can find him
      there.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5595044466688
    m_Localized: Okay. Thank you, Victor. You're a good person.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5614438928384
    m_Localized: Good day to you, Anna. And I'm sure Artyom is still alive. Cheer
      up.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5633669812224
    m_Localized: Certainly.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6601912307712
    m_Localized: "\u2026"
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6382302744576
    m_Localized: Good afternoon. I need to speak with you about my husband, Artyom.
      I've heard he used to visit your shop often, well... before he disappeared.
      I think he was asking you about artifacts related to the early eras in the
      Urals, especially B.C. Do you happen to remember him?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6499239940096
    m_Localized: "Yes, I think I do. \u2014 It's been quite a while since I last
      saw him. Your husband is an extremely interesting conversationalist, and people
      like me often find themselves lacking exactly that kind of company. Well, you
      know what I mean: I don't exactly get many visitors."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6512695267328
    m_Localized: Yes, yes. And did Artyom perhaps ask about or look for anything
      specific?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6525982822400
    m_Localized: Well, he was often interested in finds related to ancient tribes,
      or even some specific people, I would say, or perhaps even an entire civilization.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6539803054080
    m_Localized: Which tribes are you talking about? Some specific people in the
      ancient Urals? And did he mention anything he managed to find or was planning
      to research in more detail?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6555242287104
    m_Localized: He was looking for traces of some ancient civilization. And it seemed
      he was convinced that tribes existed in the Urals that were similar in some
      aspects of their beliefs to the Aryans, and perhaps even much more developed
      than we imagine. Your husband believed that these people left behind tools
      and implements that didn't just surpass their time. Some technologies were
      inherited by their descendants, but most of them disappeared without a trace,
      as did almost all mentions of their culture. He was captivated by this. He
      wanted to prove that this civilization didn't vanish by chance, but was destroyed
      or disappeared for some inexplicable reason. That very reason was what Artyom
      was primarily searching for.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6571444883456
    m_Localized: 'I... I couldn''t help him. He spent a lot of time studying those
      old tools, but never managed to figure out which people lived here. Or why
      their technologies were so advanced for that era. And, of course, what primarily
      concerned Artyom was: why and where did they go?'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6587014139904
    m_Localized: He didn't find anything at all? There must have been some leads.
      Did he intend to find something specific and study it more closely on site?
      Did he mention anything?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6647881879552
    m_Localized: There is one place I suggested to him before he left. An old museum,
      'Arkaim'. It's been closed for a long time, but... Perhaps there are still
      some traces there that could help him pick up the trail. But I'm not sure he
      could find anything else there. The place has been abandoned for a long time,
      and, frankly, all that's there is dust and remnants of the past.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6662914265088
    m_Localized: The Arkaim Museum? Where is it?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6676038242304
    m_Localized: It's on the outskirts, in the abandoned part of the city beyond
      Chistopolskaya. About 5 kilometers further down the road. No one has lived
      nearby for a long time. It's a remote area, and there were severe fires about
      a hundred years ago. There were strange incidents. People still speculate about
      them. I recall reading that even scientists from all over the world came to
      study the phenomenon. They say that a couple of times, fire just ignited there
      in the air, out of nowhere.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6688080089088
    m_Localized: Do you think Artyom went there after all?
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6698884616192
    m_Localized: Well, at that point, it seemed to me, he had hit a dead end and
      was desperately looking for any leads for his investigation of antiquity. And
      if he did go there and didn't return, then perhaps he found clues to his theories.
      Although, I admit, I told him about that museum just to offer some support.
      There was almost no chance that anything could actually be found there.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6709156466688
    m_Localized: Still, thank you for the information. I think I'll go there anyway.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6729792442368
    m_Localized: Don't lose hope. If Artyom disappeared, then apparently he did find
      the clues he needed. And if so, then you can find them too. And then you'll
      find him as well.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6740324339712
    m_Localized: Our first trip was not long, but the most exciting... Artyom, I
      miss you.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6753750306816
    m_Localized: My first gift; it seemed so silly, but Artyom cherishes it to this
      day...
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 10009553620992
    m_Localized: Is it dust? Yes, I should remember to wash it off tonight.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 10095088062464
    m_Localized: For some reason, Artyom doesn't like storing his thoughts on devices.
      Even though it's old-fashioned, I'm glad he found my gift useful.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 10164881281024
    m_Localized: When was the last time I filled it up? It seems like it's been six
      months since Artyom did it.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 10604037492736
    m_Localized: It was wrong to agree with his research. The ancient Urals had become
      his new obsession; Artyom was simply obsessed with it.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 10464824348672
    m_Localized: "Official Notification. \nFrom: Investigative Department \nDate:
      06/05/2322. \nFor: Anna Kerman \nSubject: Declaration of Artyom Kerman as missing
      \nDear Anna Kerman We hereby \nnotify you that, following lengthy and thorough
      investigative actions conducted by the investigative authorities, and in accordance
      with established procedure, your husband, Artyom Kerman, has ultimately been
      declared missing. \nDespite all efforts to establish his whereabouts, as well
      as numerous search operations, no evidence regarding his fate or whereabouts
      that could confirm his survival has been obtained. During the investigation,
      which included collecting statements, inspecting potential locations, and testing
      various hypotheses, not a single significant lead was discovered."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 10527902486528
    m_Localized: "In accordance with the law, Artyom Kerman is declared missing 90
      days after the official request, given the lack of information regarding his
      fate and the active absence of any traces. All further legal proceedings and
      possible actions in the case will depend on the discovery of new information.
      \nIf you have any additional questions or receive new information, please immediately
      contact the investigative department where this case was registered. We also
      remind you that you can contact us shortly to clarify further steps in your
      case. \nWe hope for your understanding and offer our sincere condolences in
      connection with this situation. \nSincerely, (Signature) \nInvestigator Latnikov
      A.V. \nInvestigative Department of the city of Chelyabinsk, 45th International
      Street 51."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 11993220337664
    m_Localized: 'Did crabs of this size actually live in temperate latitudes? Wait,
      there seems to be a note about the finder and archaeologist: umm... so... Brod
      Tovard?'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12043950444544
    m_Localized: It seems that in ancient times there were tribes that knew how to
      harvest spider silk for crafting needs... A looot of spider silk...
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12056940204032
    m_Localized: 'Hold on: what is a crowbar doing in a museum display case from
      ancient eras?'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12074224930816
    m_Localized: Did carts with wheels like these really exist? I've heard about
      war chariots, but I imagined them differently...
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12091505463296
    m_Localized: 'What''s this, ancient writing? What does it say: Mok Ra? Zag-Zag?
      I can''t make it out...'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12111898169344
    m_Localized: "They foisted off some old arcade machines from Pushkin Park on
      us for god knows what reason. They're still in the basement for now. On my
      break, I decided to test one of them: it still works! Now there's at least
      some entertainment. Except I accidentally dropped a sheet of paper with my
      login passwords into it \u2014 our security team uses such crazy passwords,
      you can never remember them. Well, I figure nothing will happen: it's unlikely
      anyone would think to go looking for them inside an arcade machine, and it
      would only spit them out if someone got consecutive wins on all levels, and
      I can't be bothered with that kind of hardcore."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12191724163072
    m_Localized: Max, on behalf of the security service, I again express my sincere
      admiration for your ability to find the only working object in a museum after
      midnight. I'm especially impressed by how quickly you respond to the arcade
      machine's 'threats' and protect it from dust. However, my monitors and security
      cameras have been calling me, complaining about how rudely you abandoned them,
      trading them for some ancient junk. I think we all agree that 8-bit sound is
      the most suitable 'atmospheric background' for a museum. But the surveillance
      systems are jealous and refuse to tolerate it, threatening to take legal action.
      For now, I'm holding off their attacks, but I won't last long. If you don't
      tone down your heroism in fighting the machine, I'm afraid we might lose this
      battle. I think you should stop trying to set a new record until the end of
      your shift. Otherwise, the arcade machine will be officially declared the most
      disciplined employee of the month, and I'll have to explain why it will be
      receiving your salary instead of you. Sincerely, your beloved boss.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12239807664128
    m_Localized: "Dear colleagues, please do not let that crazy person into the museum
      anymore. The other day he was shouting again about doors to the past and the
      master race that is watching us from 'behind the veil of time'. Maybe I'm no
      Einstein, but we don't need any of that crap. And most importantly, this guy
      always leaves the taps in the bathroom running, as if we're stacking bills
      in there instead of toilet paper. If you miss him, you can identify him by
      his behavior: he scurries around the main hall like a madman, muttering under
      his breath, sometimes picks something out of the trash bin and throws it back.
      And yes, for the love of all gods, do not discuss his theories about the end
      and beginning of the world with him. Escort him to my office or straight outside
      if he resists. It was funny only the first 513 times, but now he's annoyed
      everyone. At least he doesn't come often, usually only on Tuesdays and Fridays
      \u2014 otherwise our sign would soon be mistaken for a madhouse with such collaborations.
      Regarding the water \u2014 check the bathroom every two hours: that damn ninja
      sometimes seems to know all the blind spots of the security cameras! P.S. Science
      fiction is no excuse to leave taps running! Sincerely, Head of Security."
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12255209148416
    m_Localized: Hmm, this might come in handy.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12279972319232
    m_Localized: Seems like nothing interesting here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 36865673744384
    m_Localized: next
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12382917316608
    m_Localized: I remember when Artyom was deep in thought, he would often twirl
      this in his hand like a propeller. He once remarked that this pen has an amazing
      balance.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12396074848256
    m_Localized: Artyom often wore these on his forehead. I still remember how he
      laughed for a long time when I called him an antique pilot.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12409697947648
    m_Localized: Seems like nothing useful here
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12469521305600
    m_Localized: Hmm, I doubt anything here will be of use to me.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12487946883072
    m_Localized: Interesting, of course, but right now Artyom might be in danger,
      I shouldn't linger.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12512374509568
    m_Localized: I feel like I'm missing something
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12567433138176
    m_Localized: I need to keep searching, there must be clues left here
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12370065969152
    m_Localized: That crazy guy was shouting something about doors to the past, and
      that the master race behind the veil of time is watching us, that we might
      be in danger. Ugh, these lunatics have completely lost their minds with their
      sci-fi; plus, he kept leaving all the bathroom taps running and scurried around
      the second hall like our budget is made of rubber, throwing away two months'
      salary on water bills.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  references:
    version: 2
    RefIds: []
